To Compile in current directory (carma/antenna/common/Test):

% g++ -g -I. -I../../../../ -o getaframe getaframe.cc fg.cc

see bttv.README and it must have the cPCI framegrabber installed with the
video feed connected to the "top" BNC connector.  That is input "1".

% ./getaframe > test.pnm

Now you can use the netpbm tools to convert the image into something usable
by say, a web browser:

% pnmtopng test.pnm > test.png


